  "title": "Systems Engineer, Workplace M365 (Ref 26321)",
  "description": "<p>Responsibilities<br />• Respond to and resolve service desk tickets in a timely and efficient manner. <br />• Continuously monitor alerts from endpoint management tool. <br />• Provide second and third-level technical support to end users for software/ applications, hardware, and  network issues. <br />• Assist with the installation, configuration, and maintenance of IT equipment and software. <br />• Set up and configure workstations for new employees, including installing necessary software and  peripherals. <br />• Perform regular maintenance and updates on systems/ workstations within the workplace scope to  ensure optimal performance. <br />• Work closely with other IT team members and departments to resolve complex technical issues. <br />• Communicate effectively with end users to understand their needs and provide appropriate solutions. <br /><br />Requirements<br />• Bachelor’s degree or Diploma in Information Technology, Computer Science, or a related field. <br />• 5+ years of experience in end-user computing or a similar role. <br />• Familiarity with cloud services and solutions (e.g., Microsoft 365. Office 365, Azure, AWS). <br />• Strong knowledge of Windows and macOS operating systems. <br />• Experience with endpoint management solutions such as Microsoft SCCM, Intune, Ivanti or similar. <br />• Familiarity with virtual desktop infrastructure (VDI) solutions like VMware Horizon, Microsoft Cloud PC, Workspace One or Citrix. <br />• Understanding of network fundamentals, including TCP/IP, DNS, and DHCP. <br />• Excellent troubleshooting and problem-solving skills. <br />• Strong communication and interpersonal skills. <br />• Ability to work independently and as part of a team. <br />• Required certifications such as Certified: CompTIA A+, M365 Fundamentals, Microsoft Endpoint  Administrator Associate. <br />• Relevant certifications such as Certified: Azure Administrator Associate, Microsoft Certified: <br />• SharePoint, AWS Certified Cloud Practitioner, AWS Certified AI Practitioner or similar are a plus. <br />• In-depth Knowledge of SharePoint, Microsoft Purview, DLP, Microsoft Defender, AWS Connect. <br />• In-depth Knowledge of automation tool such as Power Automate. <br />• In-depth Knowledge of scripting languages such as PowerShell. <br />• Experience with mobile device management (MDM) solutions. <br />• Experience with IT service management frameworks like ITIL with ITIL V3/V4 Foundation. </p><p></p><p>Licence no: 12C6060</p>",
